lapbCountersTable.name: lapbCountersTable
lapbCountersTable.description: Runtime counters table, one row per port

lapbCountEntry.name: lapbCountEntry
lapbCountEntry.description: The set of counters for one port. Can be reset to 0.

lapbCountPortRef.name: lapbCountPortRef
lapbCountPortRef.description: The port number, the same as lapbParmPortRef from the lapbParmTable.

lapbCountRetransmis.name: lapbCountRetransmis
lapbCountRetransmis.description: The number of times a frame has been retransmitted

lapbCountSABMTxs.name: lapbCountSABMTxs
lapbCountSABMTxs.description: The number of Set Asynchronous Balanced Mode frames sent

lapbCountSABMRxs.name: lapbCountSABMRxs
lapbCountSABMRxs.description: The number of Set Asynchronous Balanced Mode frames received

lapbCountDISCTxs.name: lapbCountDISCTxs
lapbCountDISCTxs.description: The number of Disconnect frames sent

lapbCountDISCRxs.name: lapbCountDISCRxs
lapbCountDISCRxs.description: The number of Disconnect frames received

lapbCountDMsTxs.name: lapbCountDMsTxs
lapbCountDMsTxs.description: The number of Disconnected Mode frames sent

lapbCountDMsRxs.name: lapbCountDMsRxs
lapbCountDMsRxs.description: The number of Disconnected Mode frames received

lapbCountRNRsTxs.name: lapbCountRNRsTxs
lapbCountRNRsTxs.description: The number of Receiver Not Ready frames sent

lapbCountRNRsRxs.name: lapbCountRNRsRxs
lapbCountRNRsRxs.description: The number of Receiver Not Ready frames received

lapbCountUATxs.name: lapbCountUATxs
lapbCountUATxs.description: The number of Unnumbered Acknowledgement frames transmitted.

lapbCountUARxs.name: lapbCountUARxs
lapbCountUARxs.description: The number of Unnumbered Acknowledgement frames received.

lapbCountRRTxs.name: lapbCountRRTxs
lapbCountRRTxs.description: The number of Receiver Ready frames transmitted.

lapbCountRRRxs.name: lapbCountRRRxs
lapbCountRRRxs.description: The number of Receiver Ready frames received.

lapbCountFRMRTxs.name: lapbCountFRMRTxs
lapbCountFRMRTxs.description: The number of Frame Reject frames sent.

lapbCountFRMRRxs.name: lapbCountFRMRRxs
lapbCountFRMRRxs.description: The number of Frame Reject frames received.

lapbCountBadCRCTxs.name: lapbCountBadCRCTxs
lapbCountBadCRCTxs.description: The number of frames sent with bad CRC.

lapbCountBadCRCRxs.name: lapbCountBadCRCRxs
lapbCountBadCRCRxs.description: The number of frames received with bad CRC.

lapbCountAbortTxs.name: lapbCountAbortTxs
lapbCountAbortTxs.description: The number of frames sent with Abort indication.

lapbCountAbortRxs.name: lapbCountAbortRxs
lapbCountAbortRxs.description: The number of frames received with Abort indication.

lapbCountBadTypeTxs.name: lapbCountBadTypeTxs
lapbCountBadTypeTxs.description: The number of Unknown frames sent.

lapbCountBadTypeRxs.name: lapbCountBadTypeRxs
lapbCountBadTypeRxs.description: The number of Unknown frames received.

lapbCountInfoFrameTxs.name: lapbCountInfoFrameTxs
lapbCountInfoFrameTxs.description: The number of Information frames sent.

lapbCountInfoFrameRxs.name: lapbCountInfoFrameRxs
lapbCountInfoFrameRxs.description: The number of Information frames received.

lapbCountUnderrun.name: lapbCountUnderrun
lapbCountUnderrun.description: The number of times that more frames have been transmitted than the receiver can handle.

lapbCountOverrun.name: lapbCountOverrun
lapbCountOverrun.description: The number of times that the EiconCard could not handle incoming frames.

lapbCountXIDTxs.name: lapbCountXIDTxs
lapbCountXIDTxs.description: The number of Exchange Station Identification frames sent.

lapbCountXIDRxs.name: lapbCountXIDRxs
lapbCountXIDRxs.description: The number of Exchange Station Identification frames received.

lapbBandwidthTable.name: lapbBandwidthTable
lapbBandwidthTable.description: The table of configurable and informational parameters with respect to the bandwidth traps for lapb interfaces

lapbBandwidthEntry.name: lapbBandwidthEntry
lapbBandwidthEntry.description: The set of configurable and informational parameters to support the bandwidth traps for each lapb interface

lapbBandwidthIndex.name: lapbBandwidthIndex
lapbBandwidthIndex.description: The identifier of the EiconPort assigned by the agent.

lapbBandwidthHigh.name: lapbBandwidthHigh
lapbBandwidthHigh.description: The higher configurable threshold for the lapbTrapBandwidthShortage. If the percentage of bandwidth being used exceeds this amount over a configurable number of seconds (lapbBandwidthSecs) for a configurable number of consecutive periods, (lapbBandwidthNumPeriods), then the trap is sent and the lapbBandwidthTrapsStatus is changed accordingly

lapbBandwidthLow.name: lapbBandwidthLow
lapbBandwidthLow.description: The lower configurable threshold for the lapbTrapBandwidthClear. If the percentage of bandwidth being used drops below this amount, subsequent to a lapbTrapBandwidthShortage, then the trap is sent and the lapbBadwidthTrapsStatus is changed accordingly. Note that this value MUST be below that for labpBandwidthHigh

lapbBandwidthSecs.name: lapbBandwidthSecs
lapbBandwidthSecs.description: The number of seconds over which the bandwidth is calculated.

lapbBandwidthNumPeriods.name: lapbBandwidthNumPeriods
lapbBandwidthNumPeriods.description: The number of consecutive periods, each of length lapbBandwidthSecs seconds, that the condition must be present for before the lapbBandwidthShortage trap is sent.

lapbBandwidthTrapState.name: lapbBandwidthTrapState
lapbBandwidthTrapState.description: This variable indicates whether the agent should generate the lapbTrapBandwidthShortage and lapbTrapBandwidthClear traps if the relevant conditions arise. Set this value to disabled to stop these traps being generated

lapbBandwidthTrapStatus.name: lapbBandwidthTrapStatus
lapbBandwidthTrapStatus.description: The status of the bandwidth traps. This value should be polled to determine whether or not the bandwidth shortage condition is present and a trap has been sent.

lapbBandwidthRxInUse.name: lapbBandwidthRxInUse
lapbBandwidthRxInUse.description: The percentage of bandwidth that is currently in use receiving incoming traffic.

lapbBandwidthTxInUse.name: lapbBandwidthTxInUse
lapbBandwidthTxInUse.description: The percentage of bandwidth that is currently in use transmitting outgoing traffic.

lapbOperTable.name: lapbOperTable
lapbOperTable.description: This table contains configuration information about interface parameters currently set in the interface. Many of these objects have corresponding objects in the lapbAdmnTable.

lapbOperEntry.name: lapbOperEntry
lapbOperEntry.description: Currently set parameter values for a specific LAPB.

lapbOperIndex.name: lapbOperIndex
lapbOperIndex.description: The ifIndex value for the LAPB interface.

lapbOperStationType.name: lapbOperStationType
lapbOperStationType.description: Identifies the current operating station type of this interface. A value of dxe (3) indicates XID negotiation has not yet taken place.

lapbOperControlField.name: lapbOperControlField
lapbOperControlField.description: The current operating size of the sequence numbers used to number frames.

lapbOperTransmitN1FrameSize.name: lapbOperTransmitN1FrameSize
lapbOperTransmitN1FrameSize.description: The current operating N1 frame size used for the maximum number of bits in a frame this DTE can transmit. This excludes flags and 0 bits inserted for transparency.

lapbOperReceiveN1FrameSize.name: lapbOperReceiveN1FrameSize
lapbOperReceiveN1FrameSize.description: The current operating N1 frame size used for the maximum number of bits in a frame the DCE/remote DTE can transmit. This excludes flags and 0 bits inserted for transparency.

lapbOperTransmitKWindowSize.name: lapbOperTransmitKWindowSize
lapbOperTransmitKWindowSize.description: The current PDU window size this Interface uses to transmit. This is the maximum number of unacknowledged sequenced PDUs that may be outstanding from this DTE at any one time.

lapbOperReceiveKWindowSize.name: lapbOperReceiveKWindowSize
lapbOperReceiveKWindowSize.description: The current receive PDU window size for this Interface. This is the maximum number of unacknowledged sequenced PDUs that may be outstanding from the DCE/remote DTE at any one time.

lapbOperN2RxmitCount.name: lapbOperN2RxmitCount
lapbOperN2RxmitCount.description: The current N2 retry counter used for this interface. This specifies the number of times a PDU will be resent after the T1 timer expires without an acknowledgement for the PDU.

lapbOperT1AckTimer.name: lapbOperT1AckTimer
lapbOperT1AckTimer.description: The current T1 timer for this interface. This specifies the maximum time in Milliseconds to wait for acknowledgment of a PDU.

lapbOperT2AckDelayTimer.name: lapbOperT2AckDelayTimer
lapbOperT2AckDelayTimer.description: The current T2 timer for this interface. This specifies the maximum time in Milliseconds to wait before sending an acknowledgment for a sequenced PDU. A value of zero means there will be no delay in acknowledgement generation.

lapbOperT3DisconnectTimer.name: lapbOperT3DisconnectTimer
lapbOperT3DisconnectTimer.description: The current T3 timer for this interface. This specifies the time in Milliseconds to wait before considering the link disconnected. A value of zero indicates the link will be considered disconnected upon completion of the frame exchange to disconnect the link.

lapbOperT4IdleTimer.name: lapbOperT4IdleTimer
lapbOperT4IdleTimer.description: The current T4 timer for this interface. This specifies the maximum time in Milliseconds to allow without frames being exchanged on the data link. A value of 2147483647 indicates no idle timer is being kept.

lapbOperPortId.name: lapbOperPortId
lapbOperPortId.description: This object identifies an instance of the index object in the first group of objects in the MIB specific to the physical device or interface used to send and receive frames. If an agent does not support any such objects, it should return nullSpec OBJECT IDENTIFIER {0 0}.

lapbOperProtocolVersionId.name: lapbOperProtocolVersionId
lapbOperProtocolVersionId.description: This object identifies the version of the lapb protocol implemented by this interface.

lapbFlowTable.name: lapbFlowTable
lapbFlowTable.description: This table defines the objects recorded by LAPB to provide information about the traffic flow through the interface.

lapbFlowEntry.name: lapbFlowEntry
lapbFlowEntry.description: The information regarding the effects of flow controls in LAPB.

lapbFlowIfIndex.name: lapbFlowIfIndex
lapbFlowIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value for the LAPB Interface.

lapbFlowStateChanges.name: lapbFlowStateChanges
lapbFlowStateChanges.description: The number of LAPB State Changes, including resets.

lapbFlowChangeReason.name: lapbFlowChangeReason
lapbFlowChangeReason.description: The reason for the most recent incrementing of lapbFlowStateChanges. A DM or DISC frame generated to initiate link set-up does not alter this object. When the MIB-II object ifOperStatus does not have a value of testing, there exists a correlation between this object and ifOperStatus. IfOperStatus will have a value of up when this object contains: abmEntered, abmeEntered, abmReset, or abmeReset. IfOperStatus will have a value of down when this object has a value of notStarted, or dmReceived through n2Timeout. There is no correlation when this object has the value other.

lapbFlowCurrentMode.name: lapbFlowCurrentMode
lapbFlowCurrentMode.description: The current condition of the conversation.

lapbFlowBusyDefers.name: lapbFlowBusyDefers
lapbFlowBusyDefers.description: The number of times this device was unable to transmit a frame due to a perceived remote busy condition. Busy conditions can result from the receipt of an RNR from the remote device, the lack of valid sequence number space (window saturation), or other conditions.

lapbFlowRejOutPkts.name: lapbFlowRejOutPkts
lapbFlowRejOutPkts.description: The number of REJ or SREJ frames sent by this station.

lapbFlowRejInPkts.name: lapbFlowRejInPkts
lapbFlowRejInPkts.description: The number of REJ or SREJ frames received by this station.

lapbFlowT1Timeouts.name: lapbFlowT1Timeouts
lapbFlowT1Timeouts.description: The number of times a re-transmission was effected by the T1 Timer expiring.

lapbFlowFrmrSent.name: lapbFlowFrmrSent
lapbFlowFrmrSent.description: The Information Field of the FRMR most recently sent. If no FRMR has been sent (the normal case) or the information isn't available, this will be an OCTET STRING of zero length.

lapbFlowFrmrReceived.name: lapbFlowFrmrReceived
lapbFlowFrmrReceived.description: The Information Field of the FRMR most recently received. If no FRMR has been received (the normal case) or the information isn't available, this will be an OCTET STRING of zero length.

lapbFlowXidReceived.name: lapbFlowXidReceived
lapbFlowXidReceived.description: The Information Field of the XID frame most recently received. If no XID frame has been received, this will be an OCTET STRING of zero length.

lapbTrapBandwidthShortage.name: lapbTrapBandwidthShortage
lapbTrapBandwidthShortage.description: This trap indicates that the amount of bandwidth used on the specified port has risen above lapbBandwidthHigh percent over lapbBandwidthNumPeriods of lapbBandwidthSecs. The next two parameters indicate the percentage of the total bandwidth used in each direction (Transmitting or Receiving) over the last lapbBandwidthSecs number of seconds. The final parameter indicates the direction(s) in which the bandwidth threshold has been exceeded

lapbTrapBandwidthClear.name: lapbTrapBandwidthClear
lapbTrapBandwidthClear.description: This trap indicates that the condition causing a previous lapbTrapBandwidthShortage no longer applies; in particular that the bandwidth being used on the specified port has dropped to below lapbBandwidthLow percent over the last lapbBandwidthSecs number of seconds The final parameter indicates the direction(s) in which the bandwidth exceeded condition has been cleared
